It is Christmas night,<br>
My wife is asleep after working the day in a hospital,<br>
My boys are watching &quot;Star Wars&quot; on TV.<br>
And I'm reviewing new correspondence at this site.<br><br>
Yes, we do have a lot to be thankful for:<br>
We are at peace,<br>
Kids can enjoy make-believe stories,<br>
And we can enjoy each other.<br><br>
It is a time for us<br>
To simply let go,<br>
See what we have,<br>
And believe in ourselves.<br><br>
Merry Christmas<br><br>
P.S.  Charlie King was lost,<br>
Christmas Day, 1968<br>
Somewhere in Laos,<br>
Trying to save a downed pilot.
